ghamshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Stanhope","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Stanhope (Durham), from Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>hop</i> ‘valley’.","History: A family of this name have held the title Earl of Harrington since 1742, and were Earls of Chesterfield from 1628–1967. Philip Stanhope, 1st Earl of Chesterfield, was a Royalist soldier in the English Civil War. He was captured in 1643 and died in prison in 1656."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: Same as Catherine."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Katherine Stanhope was born in 1403, in Rampton, Nottinghamshire, England, her father, Richard Stanhope I, was 35 and her mother, Elizabeth Staveley, was 33. She married John de Bamburgh. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1450, in Paddlesworth, Kent, England, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1403–Abt 1450":"1403–umbes 1450","1403–1450":"1403–1450","1405–1449":"1405–1449","1425–1495":"1425–1495","1368–1436":"1368–1436","1370–1410":"1370–1410","Abt 1450":"umbes 1450","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1436":"1436","9 April 1436":"9. aprill 1436","1368":"1368","1410":"1410","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1370":"1370","1449":"1449","1405":"1405","Paddlesworth, Kent, England":"Paddlesworth, Kent, England","Wakefield, Yorkshire, England":"Wakefield, Yorkshire, England","Rampton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rampton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1403–Abt 1450":"1403–noin 1450","1403–1450":"1403–1450","1405–1449":"1405–1449","1425–1495":"1425–1495","1368–1436":"1368–1436","1370–1410":"1370–1410","Abt 1450":"noin 1450","1403":"1403","1425":"1425","1436":"1436","9 April 1436":"9. huhtikuuta 1436","1368":"1368","1410":"1410","1495":"1495","1450":"1450","1370":"1370","1449":"1449","1405":"1405","Paddlesworth, Kent, England":"Paddlesworth, Kent, England","Wakefield, Yorkshire, England":"Wakefi